TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—A Note on Including Ordinal Relations Among Multipliers in Data Envelopment Analysis
AU  - Golany, Boaz
Y1  - 1988/08/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.34.8.1029
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.34.8.1029
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1029
EP  - 1033
VL  - 34
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Data Envelopment Analysis (DEA) evaluates the efficiency of Decision Making Units without imposing a priori weights on the input and output dimensions involved. This Note extends DEA to situations where ordinal relations among weights corresponding to certain dimensions exist. The extended model is reduced to the original DEA formulation where some of the input and output factors are accumulated. An illustrative example is provided and potential areas of applications are pointed out.
AB  - Data Envelopment Analysis (DEA) evaluates the efficiency of Decision Making Units without imposing a priori weights on the input and output dimensions involved. This Note extends DEA to situations where ordinal relations among weights corresponding to certain dimensions exist. The extended model is reduced to the original DEA formulation where some of the input and output factors are accumulated. An illustrative example is provided and potential areas of applications are pointed out.
